<http://www.spektrix.com/darkehallsociety/event/41001AMGNGHKLQLCLRMPJKPQBNDVJPHRD>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Big Band Theory";
  schema:description """
	Join the <span class=\"BoldText\">Regina Jazz Orchestra</span> for our first ever <span class=\"BoldText\">“Big Band Theory”</span> concert at Darke Hall!<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Big Band Theory</span> brings Regina’s jazz community together for one electrifying night of swing, groove, and big band power. Featuring the Regina Jazz Orchestra alongside several of Regina’s outstanding high school jazz band programs, this concert celebrates both the legacy and the future of jazz in our city.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>From hard-driving swing to soulful ballads and modern big band sounds, audiences will hear musicians at every stage of their jazz journey sharing the same stage. Big Band Theory is a rare chance to experience the energy, mentorship, and community that make jazz thrive — all in one concert.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Whether you’re a longtime jazz fan or brand new to the sound, this is an evening you won’t want to miss.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">Tickets are $48.84 for adults and $15.54 for students, inclusive of fees and taxes.  Seating is not assigned.</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>
""";
