<http://www.spektrix.com/darkehallsociety/event/42601AHHMJKDLCSMPCMNQQTLCLBJSNVCP>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Conservatory Creative Camp Summer Showcase 2026";
  schema:description """
	Get ready for a very special show presented by the <span class=\"BoldText\">University of Regina Conservatory of Performing Arts Summer Creative Camps</span>.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Our <span class=\"BoldText\">Senior Glee (ages 8-12)</span> camp will present...<span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\"><span class=\"BoldText\">STAR POWER: A NEW MUSICAL</span></span><span><br/></span>By Denver Casado, Jessica Penzias, Kerry Kazmierowicztrimm, Christyn Budzyna & Jack Mitchell<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>In a galaxy obsessed with fame, flashy personas, and Cosmic Ray’s coveted “Yes Way,” a scrappy band called The Red Giants dreams of being discovered. When an unexpected opportunity puts them on the path to superstardom, they’re tempted to trade their true selves for dramatic makeovers, capes, and carefully crafted personas. As ambition pulls them apart and loyalty is put to the test, the band must decide what matters more: chasing fame or staying true to the friendships that made their music special in the first place.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">STAR POWER</span> is presented through special arrangement with Beat by Beat Press (<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bbbpress.com\">www.bbbpress.com</a>).<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>All props, costumes, set pieces and more were produced by campers in <span class=\"BoldText\">Behind the Scenes (ages 11-14)</span>. These campers will also be assisting backstage and with technical cues during the performance.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>All camps were open enrollment with no audition required!<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Doors open at 1:30pm. Shows start at 2:00pm. The approximate running time is one hour.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Rush seating. Please contact the Darke Hall box office (306-523-2751) if you have any accessibility requests, so their team can reserve appropriate seats based on your guest's needs. Darke Hall is accessible friendly.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">Tickets are $8.40 in advance or $10.50 at the door (inclusive of fees and taxes).</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Learn more about the University of Regina Conservatory of Performing Arts and join Summer Creative Camps or a variety of programs for youth and adults in Fall 2026: <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://www.uregina.ca/academics/continuing-education/conservatory-of-performing-arts.html\">Conservatory of Performing Arts</a>  <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>
""";
  schema:startDate "2026-07-25T14:00:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
  schema:image <https://system.spektrix.com/darkehallsociety/files/aedc3ca8-8884-487d-be35-db1436cd46a4.jpg>;
