  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Donovan Woods";
  schema:description """
	Thoughtful, honest, and quietly powerful, <span class=\"BoldText\">Donovan Woods</span> brings a night of storytelling through song. With his signature blend of folk and country, this is an intimate performance filled with sharp lyrics, understated humour, and songs that linger long after the final note. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>JUNO Award-winning songwriter Donovan Woods is known for his deeply personal lyrics and warm, understated sound. Blending folk and country influences, he has built a reputation as one of Canada’s most respected storytellers—crafting songs that are as relatable as they are beautifully written. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"UnderlineText\">Tickets</span>  <span><br/></span>Premium $50 | Standard $40 | Economy $30 <span><br/></span>New for 26/27: $10 Youth (under 20)<span><br/></span> <span><br/></span><span class=\"UnderlineText\">The Ultimate Pass</span><span><br/></span>Build your own Darke Hall experience with our <span class=\"ItalicText\"><span class=\"BoldText\">Ultimate Pass</span></span>!<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>For $320, choose any 8 Darke Hall Presents performances and reserve your seats at the time of purchase—giving you the flexibility to create a season that fits your interests and schedule while securing your preferred seats early.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Purchase your Ultimate Pass by October 30 and receive complimentary coat check for the entire season as a thank you for supporting Darke Hall early in the season.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Every ticket supports the ongoing work of Darke Hall and helps keep this historic stage alive. 
""";
