  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Kellie Loder";
  schema:description """
	With a voice that stops you in your tracks, <span class=\"BoldText\">Kellie Loder</span> delivers a powerful night of folk-pop rooted in honesty, heart, and connection. Blending soaring melodies with deeply personal storytelling, this is a performance that moves effortlessly from intimate to electrifying—leaving audiences feeling something real. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>JUNO Award nominee <span class=\"BoldText\">Kellie Loder</span> is an East Coast singer-songwriter known for poignant lyrics and captivating live shows. Their music has earned national recognition, including multiple award nominations and high-profile features. With a gift for storytelling and connection, <span class=\"BoldText\">Loder</span> is a standout voice on the Canadian music scene. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">Event supported by OSAC</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"UnderlineText\">Tickets</span>  <span><br/></span>Premium $50 | Standard $40 | Economy $30 <span><br/></span>New for 26/27: $10 Youth (under 20)<span><br/></span> <span><br/></span><span class=\"UnderlineText\">The Ultimate Pass</span><span><br/></span>Build your own Darke Hall experience with our <span class=\"ItalicText\"><span class=\"BoldText\">Ultimate Pass</span></span>!<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>For $320, choose any 8 Darke Hall Presents performances and reserve your seats at the time of purchase—giving you the flexibility to create a season that fits your interests and schedule while securing your preferred seats early.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Purchase your Ultimate Pass by October 30 and receive complimentary coat check for the entire season as a thank you for supporting Darke Hall early in the season.<span><br/></span> <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Every ticket helps keep this stage alive with music, stories, and shared moments. 
