  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Laila Biali";
  schema:description """
	Elegant, expressive, and full of musical surprises, <span class=\"BoldText\">Laila Biali</span> brings a night of jazz-infused songwriting that moves between intimate and exhilarating. Blending virtuosity with accessibility, her performance weaves storytelling, improvisation, and reimagined favourites into a rich and engaging live experience. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>JUNO Award-winning artist <span class=\"BoldText\">Laila Biali</span> is a celebrated Canadian singer-songwriter, pianist, and broadcaster. Known for her genre-crossing sound, she blends jazz with pop, indie, and classical influences. A dynamic performer and host of CBC Music’s <span class=\"ItalicText\">Saturday Night Jazz</span>, she continues to captivate audiences across the country. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">Event supported by OSAC</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"UnderlineText\">Tickets</span>  <span><br/></span>Premium $50 | Standard $40 | Economy $30 <span><br/></span>New for 26/27: $10 Youth (under 20)<span><br/></span> <span><br/></span><span class=\"UnderlineText\">The Ultimate Pass</span><span><br/></span>Build your own Darke Hall experience with our <span class=\"ItalicText\"><span class=\"BoldText\">Ultimate Pass</span></span>!<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>For $320, choose any 8 Darke Hall Presents performances and reserve your seats at the time of purchase—giving you the flexibility to create a season that fits your interests and schedule while securing your preferred seats early.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Purchase your Ultimate Pass by October 30 and receive complimentary coat check for the entire season as a thank you for supporting Darke Hall early in the season.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Every ticket supports the artists and the experiences that bring us together.
