<http://www.spektrix.com/darkehallsociety/event/42401AMGVRNMTBVGKTCVLCNVTMNDSPQQG>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Regina Musical Club - Duo Cordelia";
  schema:description """
	As <span class=\"BoldText\">Duo Cordelia, violinist Vanessa Marcoux and pianist Marie-Christine Poirier</span> invite you into an unexpected musical landscape, where classical compositions mingle with fresh repertoire, playful improvisation, and unconventional technique.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Both graduates of the Université de Montréal and individually recognized as talented musicians, the two have been curating captivating performances together for almost a decade. Their 2024 album “Cendres” was honoured with an Opus Award for Album of the Year in the ancient, classical, romantic, modern and postmodern category.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Wander with Vanessa and Marie-Christine through a program rich in storytelling and invention, where connections spark between genres that rarely intersect, and anything is possible.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"UnderlineText\">Tickets</span>  <span><br/></span>Advance $35 | Door $40 <span><br/></span>U of R Students & Under 18 Free (only available at the door)<span><br/></span> <span><br/></span><span class=\"UnderlineText\">Full Season Subscription & 3 Pack Passes</span><span><br/></span>Support the Regina Musical Club and save by purchasing a 6 concert full season subscription for $180 or a 3 Pack for $97.50!<span><br/></span> <span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">All prices are inclusive of fees and taxes.</span>
""";
