<http://www.spektrix.com/darkehallsociety/event/41802ADLRKJVHHQGPPMRJNCRPPHJGSJRD>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Regina Musical Club - Marco Ding, clarinet";
  schema:description """
	<span class=\"BoldText\">RMC Recital Competition Winner Marco Ding</span> is a third-year student pursuing a Bachelor’s degree in <span class=\"BoldText\">Clarinet</span> Performance at the University of Toronto, studying under Miles Haskins. Before coming to Toronto, he took part as the principal clarinet of the South Saskatchewan Youth Orchestra and the National Youth Band of Canada. He won multiple competitions and awards at the Regina and Saskatchewan Music Festivals, including the Fleming Award, Love of Music scholarship, and first place in the MLT-Aikins competition. For the past year, he has regularly performed with the Toronto Symphony Youth Orchestra and the University of Toronto Symphony Orchestra.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"UnderlineText\">Program</span><span><br/></span>André Messager, Solo de Concours<span><br/></span>Robert Schumann, Fantasiestücke<span><br/></span>He Zhanhao (arr. Marco Ding), Butterfly Lovers Fantasy<span><br/></span>Aaron Copland, Concerto for Clarinet and String Orchestra<span><br/></span>Charles-Marie Widor, Introduction et Rondo<span><br/></span>Johannes Brahms, Clarinet Sonata No.2<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"UnderlineText\">Tickets</span>  <span><br/></span>Advance $35 | Door $40 <span><br/></span>U of R Students & Under 18 Free (only available at the door)<span><br/></span> <span><br/></span><span class=\"UnderlineText\">Full Season Subscription & 3 Pack Passes</span><span><br/></span>Support the Regina Musical Club and save by purchasing a 6 concert full season subscription for $180 or a 3 Pack for $97.50!<span><br/></span> <span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">All prices are inclusive of fees and taxes.</span>
""";
